To guard against the result of precautions having a worse effect than the disease, including: promoting fear among the population, especially in children; 
prioritizing the needs of the very few over the vast majority; 
causing further environmental damage for the sake of extending the lives of a tiny proportion of the current generation of human beings eg. extra plastic being produced and discarded to adhere to government policy such as ‘disposable’ face masks and ever-changing signage.
